'''Darnley Scantlebury''', known to most as '''Donnie Scantz''', is a [[music producer]], [[musician]] and [[songwriter]].  He is the founder of State of Emergency, a [[music]] and extreme lifestyle [[allegiance]] dedicated to producing [[R&B]], [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Hip-Hop]] and [[Rock music|Rock]]. He is a two time [[Grammy Nominees|Grammy Nominee]] and has worked with artists such as [[Aaliyah]], [[Toni Braxton]], [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]], [[Ludacris]], [[J. Holiday]], [[Danity Kane]] and [[Chris Brown (American singer)|Chris Brown]].

== Education ==
Scantz graduated from the [[High School for Performing and Visual Arts]] (HSPVA) in [[Houston, Texas]]<ref>Cronin, Peter. "[http://www.sesac.com/pdf/focus_summer_2004.pdf Donnie Scantz to the Rescue]." ''[[SESAC|SESAC Focus]]''. Summer 2004, Volume VX, No. 2.</ref> and continued his education at  [[Howard University]].{{citation needed|date=September 2008}}

==Awards and nominations==
In 2003, Donnie Scantz won the [[Dove Award]] for his work with [[Out of Eden]]'s This Is Your Life. In 2004, he received two [[Grammy]] Nominations for [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]]'s ''[[Confessions (Usher album)|Confessions]]''.

